%% GitHub Collaboration Flow (Fork → Clone → Branch → PR → Merge)
%% Shows complete open source contribution workflow

graph TB
    Original[Original Repository<br/>github.com/teacher/project] --> Fork[Fork Button]
    Fork --> YourFork[Your Fork<br/>github.com/student/project]
    
    YourFork --> Clone[git clone]
    Clone --> Local[Local Repository<br/>on your computer]
    
    Local --> Branch[git checkout -b<br/>feature-new-button]
    Branch --> Edit[Make changes<br/>Edit files]
    Edit --> Add[git add .]
    Add --> Commit[git commit -m<br/>'Add new button']
    Commit --> Push[git push origin<br/>feature-new-button]
    
    Push --> YourForkBranch[Your Fork<br/>feature-new-button branch]
    YourForkBranch --> PR[Create Pull Request]
    PR --> Review{Code Review}
    
    Review --> |Request changes| Edit
    Review --> |Approve| Merge[Merge to Original]
    Merge --> Original
    
    Original --> Sync[Keep fork synced<br/>git pull upstream main]
    Sync --> Local
    
    style Original fill:#fce4ec
    style YourFork fill:#e8f5e9
    style Local fill:#f0f7ff
    style Branch fill:#fff3e0
    style Edit fill:#fff3e0
    style Add fill:#fff3e0
    style Commit fill:#fff3e0
    style Push fill:#fff3e0
    style PR fill:#fff9e6
    style Review fill:#fffde7
    style Merge fill:#e8f5e9

